189
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:40,400
And I was reading the grant proposal and some of the impact of the work that she had done.

190
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:46,400
And I was completely fangirling. I believe it was PyCon in Portland in 2016.

191
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:51,400
I was doing my recruitment looking for directors to contact, and I just started talking to her on Twitter.

192
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:55,400
I was like, you're amazing, you're amazing. Have you ever thought about running for the board?

193
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:58,400
